{{for|the agreements between the EU and other nations|Economic Partnership Agreements}}
{{trade bloc}}
An '''economic partnership agreement''' is an [[trade agreement|economic arrangement]] that eliminates [[trade barrier|barriers]] to the free movement of [[Good (economics)|goods]], [[Service (economics)|services]], and [[investment]] between countries. This agreement can be considered an intermediate step between [[free trade area]] and [[single market]] in the process of [[economic integration]]. Economic partnerships are sometimes described as ''high standard'' variants of free trade agreements.

One example is the Japan-Mexico Economic Partnership Agreement.<ref>http://www.mofa.go.jp/POLICY/economy/fta/mexico.html</ref>
